td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Newbie Hate Raid</span><hr size=1> Got a question for ya, its been forever since Ive been up in Hate.. Way before they added the 2nd floor stuff and minibosses and such.. Anyhow, I dont remember being hate too difficult as far as the first floor went.. What would be the minimum requirements for a small raid to go up there just to see how well they do? Im not sure whats really different now to the first floor and if it would make it too hard for us to do.. How do you think 2-3 groups of people 46-53 would fair? Im not talking about a big hate raid and clearing the whole 1st floor, maybe just pulling a few houses just for fun and to gage how well we do, Id hate to have an instant wipeout though which is why I ask. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/29/02 11:21:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11670.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Hate Raid</span><hr size=1> Just a warning, since the patch hate break in is now much harder, you may have a level 63 mob jump you at the entrance.  Have fun!<br>
