 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utarfcrackleberry.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tarf Crackleberry</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/30/02 10:50:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11670.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Hate Raid</span><hr size=1> The big dark elf did not aggro us on break in either of the two times we have been since the patch.<br>
<br>
One thing you should be concerned about is that Hate was revamped totally.  All the mobs were made more difficult.  In addition, a trap was placed in SW Corner, so that spot is no longer safe.<br>
<br>
I believe 2 to 3 groups would get owned, unless your chanters are very very good.<br>
<br>
we went patch night and had a 53 chantress and 3 groups, including 60 monk.  We broke in fine and had no problems.  Went back on Saturday with a different group and had a 56 chanter and wiped on port in.  We had 4 groups on Saturday.  The groups on Saturday were higher level.  Invis dropped early and we had some problems in the portup area.<br>
<br>
I think you will have problems with the level range you are taking up there.  If they are excellent players, then you may be okay.  It only takes one screw up to wipe your raid out though.<br>
<br>
were you planning on breaking in at the port up room or the south west camp?<br>
<br>
Tarf<br>
60 cleric<br>
Harfa <br>
53 Rogue <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujubaltorv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jubal Torv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/31/02 1:02:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11670.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Hate Raid</span><hr size=1> Break in at the zone in point was easy yesterday with a well balanced group of 60s. The big dark elf fella was near but didn't add on break, we pulled him a little later. He was very gimp for a red mob, and his loot was even gimpier... bog 17/35 1hs SK weapon <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubotielemonade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Botie Lemonade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/31/02 1:32:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11670.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Hate Raid</span><hr size=1> So the revamped planes dont just include the new second floor area, but the 1st floor area got a big upgrade in hate? Same for fear Im guessing? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/31/02 3:18:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11670.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Hate Raid</span><hr size=1> The hate changes to the lower floor are very recent.  Nasty surprise to a guild raid that hit Hate on Firiona Vie... they got smashed by 5 spite golems and the Deathrot Knight.  Needless to say, they took a real beating on the break in.<br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel<br>
Firiona Vie <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ueldryc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eldryc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/31/02 11:23:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11670.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Hate Raid</span><hr size=1> something besides adding this big dark elf was changed in Hate recently?  The only definite change I've heard about is the dark elf.  I assumed when people said the difficulty otherwise was raised, they were referring to the revamp that happened a long time back.  I doubt 5 spite golems are routinely parked by the zone in.  I've been on a raid where something weird like that happened to but that was months ago.  There was no one else in teh zone before we ported up.  Our first group ported up and stood right at zone in.  Within 30 seconds, 6-8 mobs including the treasure chests (so it wasn't all wanderers) came charging in and slaughtered us.  I don't know what happened that time, but it's not the norm.  Usually you can port up, take a right out of the gatehouse to the wall and run the wall around until you're just north of the SW corner.  Run maybe 1/2 to 2/3rds of the way up the wall.  Too high and you could aggro the 2nd floor.  Come down off the wall north of the SW corner to avoid the imps.  Anyone who is aggro'ed along the way should stand and die.  That's the biggest problem when taking lower levels up there.  No matter how many times you tell them, someone always brings their train to the camp spot and wipes everyone.  <br>
<br>
-- Callon<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulardmasta.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lard Masta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/02 8:42:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11670.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Hate Raid</span><hr size=1> break in can be a bitch sometimes, just depends on the luck or the draw, you can get say 3 easy abs or 3 golems + lots of roaming crap, if your going up below 55 i wouldnt recomend doing a port in break since the agro range is pretty wide and your likely to get swamped with more than you can handle very quickly.<br>
<br>
The DE guy didnt agro onto us at port in, but did when i was pulling the mini-bosses in the large two floor building, i didnt see where it came from, just warped ontop of my pull wiht a bunch of adds, nothing too hard for a group or two of 60s, could be different for people lower than 55.<br>
<br>
And dont foget to dispel golems!! sometimes you even forget when yer 60 and you wipe because of it /cough <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umerkez.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merkez</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/02 9:53:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11670.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Hate Raid</span><hr size=1> There are many ways to &quot;break&quot; the plane of hate, home of innoruuk, and they have varied over time.<br>
<br>
<br>
There are as it is now, 3 different places to break it from, with varying popularities and difficulties.<br>
<br>
The 3 spots are:<br>
<br>
&quot;West wall&quot;<br>
&quot;NE corner&quot;<br>
&quot;Zone in&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
The difficulty with west wall and ne corner is now cause they added mobs on the second floor, and if you are unlucky and not careful you can aggro the mobs from the second floor if you are sitting on the first floor walls.<br>
<br>
So simply, the easiest, and the best way to break into the plane of hate is the gate in point.<br>
<br>
When you gate in, you turn 180 degrees, take 4 steps forward, and stay at the corner where the door is, on your right hand side, this way the roamers that roam behind the wall straight where you pop in from the GG wont aggro.<br>
<br>
